      "content": "but that's just being a spectator, isn't it? just existing to consume things and occupy space until the body eventually fails. it feels so hollow. if the \"me\" that mattered—the one that felt, and created, and was alive—is already gone, then what's the point of clinging to this empty vessel? isn't there a certain kind of peace in just accepting that the story is over?",
